Charles CASAZZA, Plaintiff Appellant, v. Palmer CANFIELD, Individually, etc., Defendant Appellee. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. December 9, 1925.) No. 139. Keron F. Dwyer, of New York City, for appellant. Emory R. Buckner, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Robert B. Watts, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before ROGERS, MANTON, and HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed in open court.
